      "content": "**[SCENE START]**\n\n**INT. EMERGENCY BAY - DAY**\n\nThe overly decorated, ridiculous office has violently snapped away. We are now in a sterile, brightly lit, high-tech EMERGENCY BAY. The air is crisp, professional. NURSE (30s, sharp, calm, radiating competence) stands beside a gurney where PATIENT (any age, looking worried) is seated.\n\nThe quacking bravado has been replaced by clinical urgency.\n\nNURSE\n(Voice is immediately calm, direct, and authoritative. She gently places a hand on the Patient's arm.)\nHold up there. Forget the insulin for a minute. We need to get a baseline reading first.\n\nShe glances at the Patient, her expression serious.\n\nNURSE (CONT'D)\nShaky, dizzy, confused, you say? Sounds like your sugar is having a little chat with itself. We need to check that immediately.\n\nShe swiftly pulls out a glucometer.\n\nNURSE (CONT'D)\nDo *not* dose anything until we know if you’re running high or low. Sit tight, take a deep breath for me. We’ll get this number fast",
